The article discusses how small business owners in Cincinnati were burdened by taxes and how the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act signed by President Donald Trump has provided relief for them. The act allows small businesses to deduct 20 percent off their business income and have their taxable income taxed at lower rates. It also allows them to write off investments in new equipment. The article mentions that small business owners are now using their tax savings to make investments in their businesses, such as buying new equipment, expanding services, and hiring more employees. The author, the head of the U.S. Small Business Administration, believes that this is a golden age for small businesses, with low unemployment rates, high job openings, and positive outlook for finding quality jobs.